For-profit schools date all the way
back to colonial times. Not everyone

00:10:01.050 --> 00:10:05.190
could attend institutions like Harvard,
so entrepreneurs saw a business

00:10:05.190 --> 00:10:09.390
opportunity and began teaching reading, writing
and trade skills *** for a

00:10:09.390 --> 00:10:14.130
fee. Benjamin Franklin was a big
fan of for-profit schools and the

00:10:14.130 --> 00:10:20.500
practical skills they offered. In
